quran[23]{c,v,t}:
  3,52,"When Jesus sensed disbelief from them, he said, “Who are my helpers in the cause of Allah?” The disciples said, “We are helpers of Allah. We believe in Allah; so bear witness that we are Muslims.”"
  3,53,"“Our Lord, we believe in what You have sent down and we follow the messenger; so count us among those who bear witness [to the truth].”"
  3,54,"And [the disbelievers] devised a plan, but Allah also made a plan, and Allah is the best of planners"
  3,55,"And [remember] when Allah said, “O Jesus, I will take you and raise you up to Myself and deliver you from those who disbelieve, and make those who follow you above those who disbelieve until the Day of Resurrection. Then you will all return to Me, and I will judge between you concerning that over which you differed"
  3,56,"As for those who disbelieve, I will punish them severely in this world and the Hereafter, and they will have no helpers"
  3,57,"As for those who believe and do righteous deeds, He will give them their rewards in full, and Allah does not like the wrongdoers.”"
  3,58,This is what We recite to you of the verses and wise reminder
  3,59,"The similitude of Jesus before Allah is like that of Adam; He created him from dust, then said to him, “Be,” and he was"
  3,60,"This is the truth from your Lord, so do not be of those who doubt"
  3,61,"Whoever disputes with you concerning him [Jesus] after the knowledge has come to you, then say, “Come, let us call our sons and your sons, our women and your women, ourselves and yourselves, then invoke the curse of Allah upon the liars.”"
  3,62,"Indeed, this is the true narrative, and none has the right to be worshiped except Allah, and Allah is the All-Mighty, the All-Wise"
  3,63,"If they turn away, then Allah is All-Knowing of those who spread corruption"
  3,64,"Say, “O people of the Book, come to a common term between us and you, that we worship none but Allah and associate no partners with Him, and that we do not take one another as lords besides Allah.” But if they turn away, say, “Bear witness that we are Muslims [submitting to Allah].”"
  3,65,"O People of the Book, why do you dispute about Abraham, while the Torah and the Gospel were not sent down but after him? Do you not understand"
  3,66,"Here you are! You are those who disputed about that of which you have some knowledge, then why do you dispute about that of which you have no knowledge? Allah knows and you do not know"
  3,67,"Abraham was neither a Jew nor a Christian, but he was a monotheist Muslim, and he was not one of the polytheists"
  3,68,"The closest people to Abraham are those who followed him, and this Prophet and those who believe. And Allah is the Guardian of the believers"
  3,69,"A faction of the People of the Book wishes to mislead you [believers]; they do not mislead except themselves, but they do not realize"
  3,70,"O People of the Book, why do you disbelieve in the verses of Allah while you testify [to their truth]"
  3,71,"O People of the Book, why do you mix the truth with falsehood and conceal the truth knowingly"
  3,72,"A faction of the People of the Book say, “Believe in what has been sent down to the believers in the morning and reject it in the evening, so that they may return [from their faith]"
  3,73,"And do not believe in anyone except those who follow your religion.” Say, “The guidance is the guidance of Allah.” [They say,] Lest someone may be given similar to what you have been given or argue with you before your Lord. Say, “All bounty is in the Hand of Allah; He grants it to whom He wills. And Allah is All-Encompassing, All-Knowing.”"
  3,74,He chooses for His mercy whom He wills; for Allah is the Possessor of great bounty.”